  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Glycemic variability in critically ill patients is a recognized negative prognostic factor.
      The molecular mechanisms determining inter-patients variability in glucose metabolism during
      stress are not fully understood. The Phosphatase and Tensin homolog (PTEN) is known to
      influence glucose homeostasis by interfering in intracellular insulin signaling.

      Aim of this study is to ascertain whether differential expression of PTEN in critically ill
      patients correlates with glycemic variability and clinical outcome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
